# Goal Description
The objective is to build a complete, final web application that integrates the trained Machine Learning models ([best_model.pth](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/desktop/OPEN%20LAB/OPENLAB_PROJECT/notebooks/best_model.pth) for damage detection and [fraud_rf_model.pkl](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/desktop/OPEN%20LAB/OPENLAB_PROJECT/notebooks/fraud_rf_model.pkl) for fraud classification). The application will feature a FastAPI backend to run the AI inference and a modern, premium frontend built with React and Vite to allow users to upload images and view the fraud analysis results.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since we are skipping the full Firebase/Blockchain architecture for now to focus on the core "Final Website" with the models, I will build:
> 1. A Python **FastAPI Backend** to handle the heavy ML inference.
> 2. A **React (Vite) Frontend** with highly polished, modern CSS to serve as the user portal.
> 
> Does this approach align with exactly what you want to see right now?

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (Python/FastAPI)
The backend will serve as the AI inference engine.
#### [NEW] `backend/requirements.txt`
Dependencies including `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `torch`, `torchvision`, `pandas`, `scikit-learn`, `numpy`, `pillow`, `python-multipart`.
#### [NEW] `backend/main.py`
The FastAPI application that:
- Loads the Mask R-CNN [best_model.pth](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/desktop/OPEN%20LAB/OPENLAB_PROJECT/notebooks/best_model.pth).
- Loads the Random Forest [fraud_rf_model.pkl](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/desktop/OPEN%20LAB/OPENLAB_PROJECT/notebooks/fraud_rf_model.pkl).
- Exposes a `POST /api/predict` endpoint accepting an image file. It will run the image through the damage model, extract the 13 geometric features using your exact `extract_features` logic, run the fraud model, and return the bounding boxes, features, and fraud probability.

### Frontend (React/Vite)
A gorgeous, modern UI for the user to upload the image and view the analysis.
#### [NEW] `frontend/`
We will initialize a new React app using Vite (`npx create-vite-app`).
#### [NEW] `frontend/src/App.jsx`
The main dashboard where the user can drag and drop a vehicle image.
#### [NEW] `frontend/src/components/ImageUploader.jsx`
Component handling the image upload and preview.
#### [NEW] `frontend/src/components/AnalysisResults.jsx`
Component that parses the API response. It will draw the bounding boxes on top of the image and display a dashboard of the Fraud Score and Extracted Features.
#### [NEW] `frontend/src/index.css`
A premium Vanilla CSS stylesheet utilizing modern design trends (dark mode, glassmorphism, smooth animations) to make the app look stunning.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- We will verify the backend API by sending a sample image via a Python script or cURL to ensure it returns the correct JSON structure without crashing.
- We will verify the frontend builds successfully using `npm run build`.

### Manual Verification
- We will run the FastAPI server and the Vite dev server locally.
- We will open the application in the browser, upload a test image from the dataset, and visually verify that the bounding boxes are drawn correctly and the fraud score is displayed accurately.
